cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SI. 

This paper proposes a new inference algorithm for graph-based dependency parsing, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also utilizes state-of-the-art undirected MST algorithms, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The algorithm's efficiency is also a key focus, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
